    "InformationWhat information the board needs is highly context-specific and mainly depend on the board's responsibilities (Sect. 2).",
    "The board's structure determines what sources of information are available (Sect. 3).",
    "While internal boards have access to some information by default, external boards have to rely on public information and information the company decides to share with them.",
    "Both internal and external boards might be able to gather additional information themselves (e.g.",
    "via formal document requests or informal coffee chats with employees).Getting information from the company is convenient for the board, but the information might be biased."
